Filter features with replicated expression in some subgroup

filter_exprs_replicated_in_some_subgroup.Rd

Filter features with replicated expression in some subgroup

filter_exprs_replicated_in_some_subgroup(
  object,
  comparator = if (contains_ratios(object)) "!=" else ">",
  lod = 0
)

Arguments

object

SummarizedExperiment
comparator

'>' or '!='
lod

number

Value

Filtered SummarizedExperiment

Examples

require(magrittr)
file <- download_data('stemcells.proteinGroups.txt')
object <- read_proteingroups(file)

#> 	Read: ~/importomicscache/datasets/stemcells/stemcells.proteinGroups.txt
#> 	Prepare samples
#> 		Standardize snames: Ratio M/L normalized E(L).EM(M).BM(H).R1  ->  E(L).EM(M).BM(H).R1{M/L}
#> 		Demultiplex snames: E(L).EM(M).BM(H).R1{M/L}  ->  EM_E.R1
#> 		Read design (update if required!): ~/importomicscache/datasets/stemcells/stemcells.proteinGroups.Ratio.normalized.design.txt
#> 		Retain 9/9 samples: ~!subgroup %in% rm_subgroups
#> 	Log2 transform
#> 		Replace NaN -> NA for 12544/77643 values (in 2226/8627 features and 9/9 samples)
#> 		Log2 transform
#> 	Filter features
#> 		Retain 8528/8627 features: ~Reverse != "+"
#> 		Retain 8408/8528 features: contaminant != '+'
#> 		Retain 7877/8408 features: non-zero, non-NA, and non-NaN for some sample
#> 	Transform exprs
object %<>% filter_exprs_replicated_in_some_subgroup()

#> 		Filter 7156/7877 features: expr != 0 for at least two samples in some subgroup

file <- download_data('glutaminase.metabolon.xlsx')
object <- read_metabolon(file)

#> 	Read: ~/importomicscache/datasets/glutaminase/glutaminase.metabolon.xlsx
#> 		Guess replicate values from sampleids: UT_h10_R1 => R1
#> 		Log2 transform
object %<>% filter_exprs_replicated_in_some_subgroup()

#> 		Filter 391/391 features: expr > 0 for at least two samples in some subgroup
